    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-06-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-06-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="864"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d864">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.51/6–1847</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of North and West
                        Coast Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Wells</hi>)<note n="19"
                        xml:id="d864fn1">Addressed to Messrs. Woodward and Briggs.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-06-18">June 18,
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Rogers telephoned Livesey this morning to report that Ambassador Cooper’s
                    presentation of the Peruvian case did not favorably impress the Council; and
                    that the Council instructed Rogers to issue a firm statement denouncing the
                    offer should the Peruvians proceed on a unilateral basis.</p>
                <p>The Peruvian representative, Barreda,<note n="20" xml:id="d864fn2">Presumably
                        José Barreda Moller, an official of the Peruvian Ministry of the
                        Treasury.</note> will receive the same news when he calls at Mr.
                    Rogers’office this morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Milton K. Wells</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
